ssRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"= Yahweh-shalom"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:25","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"On that very night the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" said to him, “Take your father’s young bull and a second bull seven years old. Then tear down the altar of Baal "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 2:11","book":"Jdg","chapter":2,"verse":11,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 2:13","book":"Jdg","chapter":2,"verse":13,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 10:6","book":"Jdg","chapter":10,"verse":6,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 18:21","book":"1Ki","chapter":18,"verse":21,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 33:3","book":"2Ch","chapter":33,"verse":3,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 2:23","book":"Jer","chapter":2,"verse":23,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Zp 1:4","book":"Zep","chapter":1,"verse":4,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"text","text":" that belongs to your father and cut down the Asherah pole beside it. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jdg 2:11","book":"Jdg","chapter":2,"verse":11},{"label":"Jdg 2:13","book":"Jdg","chapter":2,"verse":13},{"label":"Jdg 10:6","book":"Jdg","chapter":10,"verse":6},{"label":"1Kg 18:21","book":"1Ki","chapter":18,"verse":21},{"label":"2Ch 33:3","book":"2Ch","chapter":33,"verse":3},{"label":"Jr 2:23","book":"Jer","chapter":2,"verse":23},{"label":"Zp 1:4","book":"Zep","chapter":1,"verse":4}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:26","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Build a well-constructed altar to the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God on the top of this mound. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 8:10","book":"Neh","chapter":8,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 27:1","book":"Psa","chapter":27,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 37:39","book":"Psa","chapter":37,"verse":39,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 10:29","book":"Pro","chapter":10,"verse":29,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 17:9–10","book":"Isa","chapter":17,"verse":9,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" Take the second bull and offer it as a burnt offering with the wood of the Asherah pole you cut down.” "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Neh 8:10","book":"Neh","chapter":8,"verse":10},{"label":"Ps 27:1","book":"Psa","chapter":27,"verse":1},{"label":"Ps 37:39","book":"Psa","chapter":37,"verse":39},{"label":"Pr 10:29","book":"Pro","chapter":10,"verse":29},{"label":"Is 17:9–10","book":"Isa","chapter":17,"verse":9}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:27","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So Gideon took ten of his male servants and did as the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" had told him. But because he was too afraid of his father’s family and the men of the city to do it in the daytime, he did it at night."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:28","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When the men of the city got up in the morning, they found Baal’s altar torn down, the Asherah pole beside it cut down, and the second bull offered up on the altar that had been built. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:29","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"They said to each other, “Who did this?” After they made a thorough investigation, they said, “Gideon son of Joash did it.”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:30","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then the men of the city said to Joash, “Bring out your son. He must die, because he tore down Baal’s altar and cut down the Asherah pole beside it.”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:31","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But Joash said to all who stood against him, “Would you plead Baal’s case for him? Would you save him? Whoever pleads his case will be put to death by morning! If he is a god, let him plead his own case because someone tore down his altar.” "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:32","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"That day Gideon was called Jerubbaal, since Joash said, “Let Baal contend with him,” because he tore down his altar."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:33","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"All the Midianites, Amalekites, and people of the east gathered together, crossed over the Jordan, and camped in the Jezreel Valley. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 17:16","book":"Jos","chapter":17,"verse":16,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 29:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":29,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 29:11","book":"1Sa","chapter":29,"verse":11,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 21:1","book":"1Ki","chapter":21,"verse":1,"letter":"d"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jos 17:16","book":"Jos","chapter":17,"verse":16},{"label":"1Sm 29:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":29,"verse":1},{"label":"1Sm 29:11","book":"1Sa","chapter":29,"verse":11},{"label":"1Kg 21:1","book":"1Ki","chapter":21,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:34","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The Spirit of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" enveloped "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit clothed; 1Ch 12:18; 2Ch 24:20"},{"kind":"text","text":" Gideon, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 3:10","book":"Jdg","chapter":3,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 11:29","book":"Jdg","chapter":11,"verse":29,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 13:25","book":"Jdg","chapter":13,"verse":25,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 14:6","book":"Jdg","chapter":14,"verse":6,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 14:19","book":"Jdg","chapter":14,"verse":19,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 15:14","book":"Jdg","chapter":15,"verse":14,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 10:6","book":"1Sa","chapter":10,"verse":6,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 16:13–14","book":"1Sa","chapter":16,"verse":13,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"text","text":" and he blew the ram’s horn and the Abiezrites rallied behind him. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jdg 3:10","book":"Jdg","chapter":3,"verse":10},{"label":"Jdg 11:29","book":"Jdg","chapter":11,"verse":29},{"label":"Jdg 13:25","book":"Jdg","chapter":13,"verse":25},{"label":"Jdg 14:6","book":"Jdg","chapter":14,"verse":6},{"label":"Jdg 14:19","book":"Jdg","chapter":14,"verse":19},{"label":"Jdg 15:14","book":"Jdg","chapter":15,"verse":14},{"label":"1Sm 10:6","book":"1Sa","chapter":10,"verse":6},{"label":"1Sm 16:13–14","book":"1Sa","chapter":16,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit clothed; 1Ch 12:18; 2Ch 24:20"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:35","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He sent messengers throughout all of Manasseh, who rallied behind him. He also sent messengers throughout Asher, Zebulun, and Naphtali, who also came to meet him."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:36","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then Gideon said to God, “If you will deliver Israel by me, as you said, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:37","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I will put a wool fleece here on the threshing floor. If dew is only on the fleece, and all the ground is dry, I will know that you will deliver Israel by me, as you said.” "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:38","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"And that is what happened. When he got up early in the morning, he squeezed the fleece and wrung dew out of it, filling a bowl with water."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:39","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Gideon then said to God, “Don’t be angry with me; let me speak one more time. Please allow me to make one more test with the fleece. Let it remain dry, and the dew be all over the ground.” "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jdg:6:40","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"That night God did as Gideon requested: only the fleece was dry, and dew was all over the ground."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]}]},"cachedAt":1783099278624}